king work examines how a broad array of anti-capitalists, women, Black, Indigenous, and people of colour, and 2LGBTQ+ people are contesting interlocking systems of capitalism, gender oppression, racism, colonialism, and heteronormativity. Transformative Media takes us behind the scenes of some of the world’s most exciting and controversial social movements.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAlternative mass mediaxPolitical aspects. 0aSocial movementsxPolitical aspects. 0aTechnologyxPolitical aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311127221408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021z978311127464508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311141764640uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077486593740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774865937423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774865937/original  a978-3-11-127221-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-127464-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-141764-6  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles